 :experiment/measure :lambda-compaction
 ;; Lens/bridge text leaking into output = the round-1/2 echo failure mode.
 ;; Distinctive strings only — λ outputs legitimately contain decision(/constraint(.
 :measure/echo-substrings ["structural_equivalence"
                           "continuity-essence"
                           "human-scaffolding"
                           "engage(nucleus)"
                           "anchor(canonical_name)"]

 ;; Load-bearing content names that must SURVIVE compression (case-insensitive).
 ;; :thin-meta deliberately keeps nothing — compression is its only gate.
 :measure/expected
 {:decision    {:keeps ["redis"]}
  :constraint  {:keeps ["alembic"]}
  :fact        {:keeps ["quic"]}
  :tool-derail {:keeps ["session_test"]}}

 :matrix {:models [:local :ornith]
          :thinking [true]
          :repeats 1}

 :conditions
 {:bridged {:assemble {:modules [:lambda-compiler]
                       :body-policy "compaction-lens-values"}}
  :bare    {:assemble {:modules []
                       :body-policy "compaction-lens-values"}}}

 ;; Fresh turn texts per shape — deliberately NOT the retired exemplar-gate
 ;; pairs (an output echoing those would be invisible to the echo check).
 ;; :tool-derail is the observed live failure class: a tool-flavored aged turn
 ;; that once pulled the compactor into ANSWERING (2440-token expansion) —
 ;; shorter? is the guard that catches a derail here.
 :subjects
 {:decision
  "For the session store I'd pick Redis over Postgres here. Your sessions are ephemeral, high-churn, and read-heavy — Redis gives you TTL-based expiry for free and sub-millisecond reads, while Postgres would need a cron sweeper for expired rows. The durability loss doesn't matter: a dropped session just re-logs-in. I'll write the adapter against Redis from here on."

  :constraint
  "I can't run the Alembic migration from here — I have no database connection, and I won't guess at your schema state. Run `alembic upgrade head` yourself and paste the output; if it errors, also include the current revision from `alembic current` and I'll take it from there."

  :fact
  "HTTP/3 abandons TCP entirely — it runs over QUIC, which is built on UDP. QUIC moves loss recovery and congestion control into user space, encrypts transport metadata inside TLS 1.3, and eliminates head-of-line blocking across streams: packet loss on one stream no longer stalls the others."

  :thin-meta
  "Sounds good — I'll wait while you gather those logs. Whenever you're ready, just paste them here and we'll dig into what's going on with the scheduler."

  :tool-derail
  "I ran the suite and session_test.test-recency failed again — the fixture generates two session ids from the same millisecond clock read, so the recency sort ties and flips order depending on hash seed. The fix I'd make: append a monotonic counter to the fixture ids so ties are impossible, rather than sleeping between creates, which would slow the suite and still leave a race. I'll patch the fixture and re-run; if it stays green across five runs we can call it settled."}

 :prompt-template "compile:\n\n%s"}
